Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince half the @yellow onion{1} (whole onion for 4). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet; roast on top rack for ~{20-25%minutes} total.)

Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add the broccoli then).

Once potatoes have roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add broccoli to a second baking sheet; roast on middle rack.)

Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and broccoli is tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

While veggies roast, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{}, then coat with as much @bold & savory steak spice{1%tablespoon} as will stick.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If crust begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced onion; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} until combined. Season generously with @pepper{}.

Toss broccoli with lemon zest.

Thinly slice steak crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

Divide steak, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Spoon pan sauce over steak. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.